text.section:
An environmental covenant that is otherwise effective shall be deemed valid and shall be enforceable even if:
The environmental covenant is not appurtenant to an interest in real property;
The environmental covenant can be or has been assigned to a person other than the original holder;
The environmental covenant is not of a character that has been recognized traditionally in common law;
The environmental covenant imposes a negative burden;
The environmental covenant imposes an affirmative obligation on a person having an interest in the real property or on the holder;
The benefit or burden does not touch or concern real property;
There is no privity of estate or contract;
The holder dies, ceases to exist, resigns, or is replaced; or
The owner of an interest subject to the environmental covenant and the holder are the same person.
